SIMPLE: springing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Springing
<hw>Spring"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process
of one who, or that which, springs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Growth; increase; also, that which springs up; a
shoot; a plant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou blessest the <qex>springing</qex> thereof.</q> <rj><qau>Ps.
lxv. 10.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Springing line of an arch</b></col> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>,
<cd>the horizontal line drawn through the junction of the vertical face
of the impost with the curve of the intrados; -- called also
<altname>spring of an arch</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Springle</ent>⟦br⟧
